.The plane-wave Born approximation(PWBA) theory.
The target deuterium was contained in a 60 mm diameter
gas cell with 2.2-mum thick Havar windows.
The purity of the (H-2)2 gas was 99.5%.
The beam currents were chosen in the 10-500-nA
range such as o keep the dead time below 3%.
Two dE-E telescopes. The delta-E counters
were commercial silicon surface-barrier detectors,
100-400 mum thick.
The E-counters were 25 mm long side-entry Ge(Li)
detectors.A Ge(Li) monitor detector was placed at a
fixed angle of -30-degree.

efficiency loss due to nuclear reactions in the Ge(Li)
detector, was estimated to be 5% for all cross section.
